<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" style=3D"font-style:no=
rmal;font-weight:500"><mark style=3D"background-color:#d9eef6;color:#15aedf=
" class=3D"has-inline-color">How to calculate GPA</mark></h2>



<p class=3D"has-text-align-center">(Step-by-step with GPA Calculator)</p>



<div style=3D"height:30px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">1. Add Your Letter Grade</h3>



<p>Enter your current grade and credits to calculate GPA. For unconfirmed g=
rades, select an estimate from A+ to F on the 4.0 scale. </p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter is-resized"><img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"htt=
ps://gpacalculator.net/wp-content/uploads/college-gpa-calculator-step-1-let=
ter-grades.png" alt=3D"College GPA Calculator Step 1 - Enter Class Grades" =
style=3D"width:520px;height:auto"></figure>
</div>


<div style=3D"height:30px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">2. Add Your Class Credits</h3>



<p>Enter the grade and credits for each class. For example, an A- grade in =
a 5 credit class, B+ grade in a 4 credit class etc. Click =E2=80=9CAdd anot=
her class=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9CAdd another semester=E2=80=9D as needed.</p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter is-resized"><img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"htt=
ps://gpacalculator.net/wp-content/uploads/college-gpa-calculator-step-2-cla=
ss-credits.png" alt=3D"College GPA Calculator Step 2 - Enter Class Credits"=
 style=3D"width:524px;height:auto"></figure>
</div>


<div style=3D"height:30px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">3. Calculate Your GPA</h3>



<p>Your overall GPA for all semesters is calculated automatically. The seme=
ster and cumulative (overall) GPA update as you enter grades. Add multiple =
semesters to track aggregate GPA. </p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image is-style-default">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img decoding=3D"async"=
 width=3D"679" height=3D"1024" src=3D"https://gpacalculator.net/wp-content/=
uploads/college-gpa-calculator-step-3-add-semester-679x1024.png" alt=3D"GPA=
 Calculator Step 3 - Enter New Semester" class=3D"wp-image-27462" style=3D"=
width:513px;height:auto"></figure>
</div>


<div style=3D"height:39px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" style=3D"font-style:no=
rmal;font-weight:500"><mark style=3D"background-color:#d9eef6;color:#15aedf=
" class=3D"has-inline-color">GPA Calculation Formula</mark></h2>



<div style=3D"height:30px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<p>The GPA formula is simple: <strong>GPA =3D <strong>(Grade Points =C3=97 =
Credit Hours) =C3=B7 Total Credit Hours</strong></strong>. Quality points c=
ome from multiplying each grade=E2=80=99s point value by the class credits.=
 For example,</p>



<p>1. A 3-credit class with an A (4.0), a 4-credit class with a B+ (3.3), a=
nd a 3-credit class with a C (2.0).</p>



<p>2. (3=C3=974.0 =3D 12) + (4=C3=973.3 =3D 13.2) + (3=C3=972.0 =3D 6) =3D =
31.2 quality points.</p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-table"><table class=3D"has-fixed-layout"><thead><=
tr><th>Course</th><th>Credits</th><th>Grade</th><th>Grade Points</th><th>Qu=
ality Points</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Course 1</td><td>3</td><td>A</=
td><td>4.0</td><td>12.0</td></tr><tr><td>Course 2</td><td>4</td><td>B+</td>=
<td>3.3</td><td>13.2</td></tr><tr><td>Course 3</td><td>3</td><td>C</td><td>=
2.0</td><td>6.0</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td><strong>10<=
/strong></td><td></td><td></td><td><strong>31.2</strong></td></tr></tbody><=
/table></figure>



<p>3. Divide 31.2 =C3=B7 10 total credits =3D <strong>3.12 GPA</strong>.</p=
>



<div style=3D"height:30px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" style=3D"font-style:no=
rmal;font-weight:500"><mark style=3D"background-color:#d9eef6;color:#15aedf=
" class=3D"has-inline-color">Edge Cases in GPA Calculation</mark></h2>



<div style=3D"height:30px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<p>Not all classes or grades count toward GPA the same way. Here are common=
 edge cases students often ask about:</p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-table"><table class=3D"has-fixed-layout"><tbody><=
tr><th class=3D"has-text-align-center" data-align=3D"center">Grade Type</th=
><th>How It Affects GPA</th></tr><tr><td class=3D"has-text-align-center" da=
ta-align=3D"center">Pass/Fail courses</td><td>Usually excluded from GPA. Pa=
ssing adds credits toward graduation but does not affect GPA.</td></tr><tr>=
<td class=3D"has-text-align-center" data-align=3D"center">Withdrawals (W)</=
td><td>A =E2=80=9CW=E2=80=9D is not factored into GPA. A =E2=80=9CWF=E2=80=
=9D (Withdraw Fail) may count as an F, depending on school policy.</td></tr=
><tr><td class=3D"has-text-align-center" data-align=3D"center">Incompletes =
(I)</td><td>Not included in GPA until a final grade is recorded.</td></tr><=
tr><td class=3D"has-text-align-center" data-align=3D"center">Retaken course=
s</td><td>Some colleges replace the old grade with the new one, while other=
s average both attempts.</td></tr><tr><td class=3D"has-text-align-center" d=
ata-align=3D"center">Transfer credits</td><td>Typically count toward degree=
 progress but not toward institutional GPA.</td></tr></tbody></table></figu=
re>



<p><em>Always check your school=E2=80=99s academic policy for exact rules, =
since GPA calculations can vary by institution.</em></p>



<div style=3D"height:30px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" style=3D"font-style:no=
rmal;font-weight:500"><mark style=3D"background-color:#d9eef6;color:#15aedf=
" class=3D"has-inline-color">GPA Scale</mark></h2>



<div style=3D"height:30px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<p>Most U.S. schools use a letter grading system, though details can vary. =
Some include grades like A+ or B=E2=80=93, while others don=E2=80=99t, and =
what counts as an A or B may differ. Certain courses also carry more weight=
 through credit hours, meaning they have a bigger impact on your overall GP=
A. This calculator adjusts for those differences by factoring in course cre=
dits.</p>



